        "option_b_result": "CORRECT - Asynchronous communication methods like project management software (e.g., Jira, Asana) with integrated messaging, discussion boards, or structured email updates are best for geographically dispersed teams. They allow team members to contribute and receive information at their convenience, overcoming time zone barriers and ensuring timely information flow without requiring simultaneous presence.",
        "option_c_result": "INCORRECT - While shared online documents are excellent for collaborative work, they primarily facilitate document collaboration, not necessarily broad, timely, and comprehensive information exchange for general project updates, which often involves narrative and diverse information types.",
        "option_d_result": "INCORRECT - Increasing daily stand-up meetings with varied times would exacerbate the time zone coordination problem, making it even more challenging for team members to consistently participate and leading to burnout or exclusion for some.",
        "process_group": "Executing",
        "knowledge_area": "Communications",
