        "concepts_to_understand": "Acquire Resources in the Initiating phase involves identifying critical physical resources and assessing high-level external acquisition options when internal resources are unavailable. This includes exploring specialized service providers or leasing options to understand feasibility, costs, and timelines. The objective is to determine whether the project's fundamental resource needs can be met, which directly impacts the project's viability and initial strategic direction. It's about finding the most effective means to get what's needed at a strategic level.",
