        "option_b_result": "INCORRECT - An all-hands meeting can be risky and ineffective. Team members who are already demotivated may be reluctant to voice concerns in a public forum, especially if they are sensitive or relate to management. This approach could exacerbate the problem rather than solve it.",
        "option_c_result": "CORRECT - Private, one-on-one interviews are the most effective way to address this sensitive situation. They provide a 'safe space' for team members to express their feelings without fear of retribution or judgment. The project manager can build trust, ask open-ended questions, and truly understand the individual and specific issues causing low morale. This method allows for a deeper and more empathetic understanding of the problem.",
        "option_d_result": "INCORRECT - A focus group, while better than a public meeting, still has the potential for group dynamics to influence individual responses. Some team members may not feel comfortable sharing their true feelings in front of their peers, especially if the issues are personal or relate to specific team members. The one-on-one interview is the most private and effective method for this specific problem.",
