        "additional_notes": "This question tests the candidate's understanding of the psychological and human resource applications of project management tools. The scenario is about a sensitive issue (low morale), which requires an empathetic and private approach. Interviews are the only option that offers this level of privacy and personalization. The two most plausible but incorrect options are the survey and the focus group. While they offer some level of privacy, they lack the personal connection and real-time interaction that are necessary to fully understand and address a sensitive issue like low morale. The question requires the candidate to understand the nuances of human behavior in a project setting.",
