        "additional_notes": "This is an easy-level question. The scenario is a classic agile retrospective setting, where a quick and democratic prioritization is needed. The phrase 'quickly prioritize' is the key. Voting is the only option that is both quick and democratic. The other options are either too slow (B, C) or counterproductive to team morale (A), making them clearly incorrect.",
