        "option_c_result": "CORRECT - The creation of a team charter is a foundational team-building activity for the forming stage. This collaborative process allows the team to collectively define their purpose, roles, communication norms, and decision-making processes, which directly addresses low trust and reluctance to participate by creating a shared understanding and a safe environment.",
        "option_d_result": "INCORRECT - Mentoring is a form of individual development and is generally part of the storming or norming phase of a project. While it can improve individual skills, it does not directly facilitate the collective bonding and establishment of a shared working environment needed during the initial forming stage.",
