        "concepts_to_understand": "The Tuckman model of team development (Forming, Storming, Norming, Performing, Adjourning). The purpose of a team charter in establishing a team's operating principles and code of conduct. The importance of creating psychological safety and trust, especially in the early stages of a project, to enable open communication and collaboration.",
        "additional_notes": "This question requires understanding the Tuckman model and applying the correct team-building technique for the specific stage described. The scenario mentions a team in the 'forming' stage with low trust. While other options might seem helpful, a team charter directly addresses the core issues of establishing norms and building trust by having the team define their own rules. The other options are either too formal or too informal to effectively address the specific need for psychological safety and a shared foundation at this stage. Creating a team charter is a proactive and structured way to move the team forward from the forming stage toward the storming and norming stages.",
