        "option_c_result": "INCORRECT - While this option is technically correct in its reasoning, it is politically naive. Directly refusing the request of an influential stakeholder, especially in a public setting, can be perceived as defiant and may damage the project manager's credibility and relationship with the sponsor. This is a confrontational approach.",
        "option_d_result": "INCORRECT - While asking for the 'why' is a good practice, it should be done as part of a more comprehensive strategy, not as the entire solution. The project manager should already have some insight into the CIO's motivations and should be prepared to offer a solution that addresses the CIO's concerns, not just ask questions. This option is a step in the right direction but is not the most complete or effective action.",
