        "option_c_result": "CORRECT - The 'walk the board' approach is a highly effective way to increase engagement in stand-ups. By focusing the discussion on a visual board of work items, the team shifts from giving individual status reports to collaboratively discussing the flow of work. This makes the meeting more interactive, relevant, and engaging, which is the root cause of the disengagement.",
        "option_d_result": "INCORRECT - Addressing individuals privately may be necessary, but it is not the first or most effective step. The project manager should first try to improve the process itself, as the disengagement may be a symptom of a poorly run meeting, not a behavioral problem with the individuals.",
        "process_group": "Executing",
