        "option_b_result": "CORRECT - This is the most direct and effective approach. The project manager needs to act as a facilitator and coach, reminding the team of the meeting's purpose and guiding them to a better behavior. By asking them to take problem-solving offline, the project manager reinforces the purpose of the stand-up while also ensuring the problems are addressed, just not in a public, time-boxed meeting.",
