        "additional_notes": "The scenario is a classic example of a poorly facilitated stand-up. The project manager's job is to course-correct the meeting's purpose. The best way to do this is to act as a facilitator and remind the team of the rules. Option B is the most professional and effective way to do this. It corrects the behavior, reinforces the rules, and empowers the team to solve their own problems in a more efficient way. The two close options are B and C, but B is a more nuanced, behavior-oriented solution, while C is a more rigid, process-oriented one that may not solve the underlying issue.",
