        "additional_notes": "This question tests a basic understanding of a daily stand-up. The most effective action is to facilitate a solution without derailing the meeting. By ensuring the two relevant parties will connect, the project manager is being proactive and empowering the team. All other options are either inappropriate for a stand-up (A), add unnecessary overhead (B), or are highly demotivating (D). This is an easy question because the correct answer aligns with the core principles of agile.",
        "difficulty_level": "easy"
