        "concepts_to_understand": "Kanban boards are an excellent tool for visualizing work, which in turn helps with prioritization. By using swimlanes or different colors for different types of work, a project manager can easily see the mix of tasks in the workflow and make informed decisions about what to work on next. This makes it a very flexible and powerful tool for teams with a high degree of work variation.",
        "additional_notes": "This is an easy question that tests the project manager's ability to apply the correct tool to a common project scenario. The scenario's emphasis on a 'constant stream of new work requests' and the need for a 'visual tool' points directly to a Kanban board. The other options are incorrect because they are either designed for a different project management approach (Scrum) or serve a different purpose entirely (WBS, AON).",
