      "question_pmp": "A project manager has been working with a team for six months. The team has transitioned from needing detailed instructions to working well together with minimal oversight. However, lately, morale has dropped due to high-pressure deadlines, and a few key team members have expressed doubts about their ability to meet the project's ambitious goals. They are still technically capable but seem to have lost their motivation. According to the Situational Leadership® model, what should the project manager do NEXT?",
