      "id": "1756657566479",
      "question_pmp": "A project manager is leading a project to implement a new enterprise resource planning (ERP) system. The project team is well-versed in the new system's technical requirements and has been trained on its functionality. However, end-users from various departments are resisting the change, openly expressing their reluctance to use the new system despite its documented benefits. According to the ADKAR® model, which stage of change is the project manager failing to address effectively?",
