        "option_c_result": "CORRECT - The ADKAR® model defines 'Desire' as the individual's personal motivation to support and participate in the change. The end-users are 'resisting the change' and are 'reluctant to use' the system, which indicates a clear lack of desire. The project manager's focus on technical training and documented benefits has not created the personal motivation needed for successful adoption.",
