      "question_pmp": "A project manager is leading a company-wide shift to a new collaboration platform. The initial communications have provided a clear and compelling business case, explaining the 'why' behind the change. Training sessions have been conducted, and all employees have been granted access to the new system. Despite this, a post-implementation survey reveals that employees are aware of the new system and its purpose, but many are still using the old platform. The root cause analysis points to a lack of personal motivation to switch. What is the MOST appropriate NEXT step for the project manager to address the issue, based on the ADKAR® model?",
