        "option_c_result": "CORRECT - The root cause analysis has identified a lack of personal motivation, which directly maps to the 'Desire' stage of the ADKAR® model. The project manager's next step must be to address this gap by creating incentives or communicating the specific, personal benefits of the change to individuals, thereby building the personal motivation needed to shift behavior.",
        "option_d_result": "INCORRECT - The scenario implies that training has been provided, and there is no indication that a lack of 'Ability' is the problem. Providing one-on-one coaching would be an inefficient and inappropriate response when the core issue is motivation, not skill.",
