        "option_b_result": "CORRECT - The scenario describes a classic conflict between high-context and low-context communication styles. A 'low-context' culture (like the 'direct and to-the-point' style) relies on explicit, written, and literal messages. A 'high-context' culture (like the 'indirect and relationship-building' style) relies on unspoken cues, relationships, and context to convey meaning. The misunderstandings are a direct result of these conflicting cultural communication patterns.",
