        "concepts_to_understand": "This question tests the core principle of Herzberg's theory: hygiene factors prevent dissatisfaction, while motivation factors create satisfaction. Once hygiene factors are met, a project manager must focus on providing motivation factors to drive performance and engagement. The lack of initiative in the scenario is a classic indicator that motivation factors are missing.",
