        "option_b_result": "CORRECT - The project manager is focusing on a 'Motivation' factor (the bonus). However, the team's feedback points to 'lack of trust' and 'micromanagement,' which are classic 'Hygiene' factors (supervision and work conditions). According to Herzberg's theory, if the hygiene factors are poor, they will lead to dissatisfaction and negate the positive effects of any motivation factors. The bonus failed because the underlying hygiene issues were not addressed, and the bonus system itself made them worse.",
        "option_c_result": "INCORRECT - While the bonus is an extrinsic motivator, the core issue described is not a simple intrinsic/extrinsic mismatch. The problem is a specific application of a motivation factor that has a negative impact on the underlying hygiene factors.",
        "option_d_result": "INCORRECT - The reward system is intended to be positive reinforcement. The team's perception of it as a source of micromanagement is the problem, but this is a consequence of the underlying hygiene issues, not the intent of the bonus itself.",
