      "id": "1756657956737",
      "question_pmp": "A project manager is mediating a conflict between the marketing department and the engineering team over the final product launch date. The marketing team wants to launch immediately to capitalize on a market trend, while the engineering team insists on a two-week delay to conduct a final round of security testing. Both teams have valid concerns, and a failure to launch on time or a security breach would be disastrous for the company. The project manager, instead of forcing a decision, facilitates a meeting where the teams jointly brainstorm a solution. They agree to a phased launch, releasing a minimum viable product to market first while the engineering team conducts the final security tests in parallel on the full system, with the final release happening two weeks later. This solution satisfies the core needs of both teams. What is the MOST accurate description of the conflict resolution model used by the project manager?",
