      "id": "1756657967851",
      "question_pmp": "The project manager has assembled a new, cross-functional team. After a few initial meetings, the project manager observes a significant amount of interpersonal friction. Team members are questioning each other's expertise, challenging ideas, and are reluctant to share information freely. The project manager has noted that the team is not yet ready to fully commit to the project's plan. According to the Drexler/Sibbet Team Performance Model, what is the MOST appropriate action for the project manager to take NEXT?",
