        "additional_notes": "This question tests the candidate's understanding of the specific domains of emotional intelligence and which one is most relevant to a specific interpersonal problem. The scenario describes a project manager who needs to intervene and de-escalate a situation. This requires more than just awareness; it requires action. The incorrect options are either about the project manager's internal state (A, D) or the observation of others (B). Only relationship management (C) is about the proactive, outward-facing action of the project manager to influence the situation for the better. The question is difficult because the options are all closely related emotional intelligence skills, forcing the candidate to choose the one that best describes the required action.",
